video_title: Motivational Interviewing: Evoking Commitment to Change
utterance_text: Hi, John. Nice to see you again. So, tell me, how are things going?

video_title: Motivational Interviewing: Evoking Commitment to Change
utterance_text: Well, doc, I know you told me that I need to lose weight. And even though the scale didn't show today, I was able to lose about 5 pounds, but then I gained it right back.

video_title: Motivational Interviewing: Evoking Commitment to Change
utterance_text: Well, I appreciate you bringing your weight to the forefront. Do you mind if we explore this issue further?

video_title: Motivational Interviewing: Evoking Commitment to Change
utterance_text: No, by all means. I know we have to discuss it.

video_title: Motivational Interviewing: Evoking Commitment to Change
utterance_text: All right. Uh, well, it sounds like you've been struggling with your weight recently. And I understand how difficult it is to lose the weight and then have it come back again. So, tell me what you did to lose that initial 5 pounds.

video_title: Motivational Interviewing: Evoking Commitment to Change
utterance_text: I started watching what I ate and I ate less. I've been eating more fruits and vegetables. I've also been walking a lot. I'm walking up to 20 minutes a day now. video_title: Motivational Interviewing: Evoking Commitment to Change
utterance_text: But you did have some success. Tell me how you felt when you lost the weight.

video_title: Motivational Interviewing: Evoking Commitment to Change
utterance_text: I felt great and I felt really proud of myself. I thought that this was something that I could do.

video_title: Motivational Interviewing: Evoking Commitment to Change
utterance_text: Okay. Well, it sounds like you realized that when you lost the weight you feel better and that it's gonna affect your overall health. So, tell me what you think changed that caused you to gain the weight back.

video_title: Motivational Interviewing: Evoking Commitment to Change
utterance_text: Well, I think it's because I've been eating more fruits and vegetables, that- that's it.

video_title: Motivational Interviewing: Evoking Commitment to Change
utterance_text: And how many servings of fruits and vegetables on average per day would you have?

video_title: Motivational Interviewing: Evoking Commitment to Change
utterance_text: To be honest, I have four or five -- four to six glasses of orange juice a day. Um, I have fruit for lunch and breakfast. I have, uh, usually one to two servings of a vegetable like lettuce or broccoli with thinner.

video_title: Motivational Interviewing: Evoking Commitment to Change
utterance_text: John, it's very important that you recognize that some fruits, but especially fruit juice can contain a huge amount of calories. Did you know that a glass of orange juice has almost as many calories as a can of cola?

video_title: Motivational Interviewing: Evoking Commitment to Change
utterance_text: No, I didn't know. Um, but doesn't the fruit- food pyramid classify, um, fruit juice as a- a serving?

video_title: Motivational Interviewing: Evoking Commitment to Change
utterance_text: You're absolutely right, but keep in mind that the food pyramid is to be used as a guideline only. When it comes to nutrition, we have to have a more personalized approach. video_title: Motivational Interviewing: Evoking Commitment to Change
utterance_text: Well, this changes quite a bit. I mean, here I'm thinking that my fruit intake is making me healthier and actually it's making me fatter.

video_title: Motivational Interviewing: Evoking Commitment to Change
utterance_text: Indeed. Let me ask you something, knowing what you know now, how important is it to you to lose the weight by decreasing the amount of juice that you're currently taking in?

video_title: Motivational Interviewing: Evoking Commitment to Change
utterance_text: Obviously, I need to cut back on the fruit juice. But boy, do I love that OJ.

video_title: Motivational Interviewing: Evoking Commitment to Change
utterance_text: Oh, I understand. Let me ask you this, on a scale from 0 to 10, 0 meaning that there's no way you can do it, and 10 meaning that you're 100% confident that you can do it, how confident are you that you'll be able to reduce the amount of juice you're currently taking in.

video_title: Motivational Interviewing: Evoking Commitment to Change
utterance_text: Um, six or seven.

video_title: Motivational Interviewing: Evoking Commitment to Change
utterance_text: All right. So, you're not a zero. So, that tells me that you've got some confidence that this is doable, this is something you certainly can do it. Why are you not a zero?

video_title: Motivational Interviewing: Evoking Commitment to Change
utterance_text: I guess it's because I know that I need to do it to lose the weight.

video_title: Motivational Interviewing: Evoking Commitment to Change
utterance_text: So, you realize, again, that if you decrease the amount of juice you're taking in, you're gonna decrease your weight, you're gonna feel better, and you're gonna impact your po- health positively?

video_title: Motivational Interviewing: Evoking Commitment to Change
utterance_text: Yes.

video_title: Motivational Interviewing: Evoking Commitment to Change
utterance_text: But you're also not a 10, and that tells me that there may be some obstacles to your success. What would it take for you to be a 10 or even an 8 or 9?

video_title: Motivational Interviewing: Evoking Commitment to Change
utterance_text: Okay. Now, if the juice was still there, can you think of anything else you could do?

video_title: Motivational Interviewing: Evoking Commitment to Change
utterance_text: I suppose I could replace it with, um, a low-calorie drink or drink more water.

video_title: Motivational Interviewing: Evoking Commitment to Change
utterance_text: Excellent. John, I get the impression that you want to stay in course with weight reduction. video_title: Motivational Interviewing: Evoking Commitment to Change
utterance_text: I'd say I didn't have any and I substituted it with, um, sugar-free drinks.

video_title: Motivational Interviewing: Evoking Commitment to Change
utterance_text: Excellent. Well, it sounds like you have a plan. Same scale, 0 to 10, how confident are you that you can, uh, make this happen?

video_title: Motivational Interviewing: Evoking Commitment to Change
Motivational Interviewing: Evoking Commitment to Change
utterance_text: I agree. All right. Well, you-you know what? I'm not gonna start any medications today. Your levels were a little bit off, but I think we can handle this from a purely lifestyle standpoint. What do you think?

video_title: Motivational Interviewing: Evoking Commitment to Change
utterance_text: Great. It sounds good to me.

video_title: Motivational Interviewing: Evoking Commitment to Change
utterance_text: Excellent. I'll see you in two weeks.

video_title: Motivational Interviewing: Evoking Commitment to Change
utterance_text: Okay.
